<H2 ALIGN="center">Frequently asked questions</H2>

<P>These are just some questions I can think of that people may ask. if
you have a question or an idea for this page, please contact me at
Andy@wharne.freeserve.co.</P>


<HR>
<P>

Q: Why won't the DNS servers verify when I try to connect?<BR>

<BR>

A:  You have to enter the primary and secondary DNS IP addresses as on
the <A HREF="tech.htm">Tech</A> page manually. You can do this in Miami
by going to "Database" in the menu on the left &amp; selecting "DNS servers"
from the drop down list at the top, clicking on "Add" &amp; entering the IP
addresses one at a time. Also un-tick "verify DNS servers" under
"TCP/IP" from the menu on the left.

</P>
<HR>
<P>

Q: Where do I change the login ID &amp; Password from the provided Miami
settings file?

<BR><BR>

A: Under "Dialer" in the menu on the left. The login ID &amp; Password
details are on the bottom right of the main window.

</P>
<HR>
<P>

Q: I get an authentication error when I try to connect

<BR><BR>

A: check your login info &amp; password is correct, remember, unlike other
ISP's you need to enter everything after the @ sign in your email
address, eg. &lt;host&gt;.freeserve.co.uk. It may also take a few
minutes for your account to become "active" after you first join.

</P>
<HR>
<P>

Q: I can't connect or get modem not responding messages

<BR><BR>

A: Did you change your serial device? the provided settings file is set
to the internal serial port &amp; you will need to change this if you have a
Surf squirrel, Hypercom or equivelent serial device, etc.

</P>
<HR>
<P>

Q: My transfer speed seems slow

<BR><BR>

A: There are a number of factors that can control this, but one to check
is the serial speed setting which is set to 38400 in the Miami settings
file provided on this site. This is to prevent problems for people using
the internal serial port. This can be changed in the Interface settings
in Miami &amp; can safely go up to 115200 with a Surf squirrel or
equivelent serial interface.

</P>
<HR>
<P>

Q: Not matter what I do, I can't seem to post mail or news, connect to
my website (via FTP for uploading/downloading) or use the IRC and game
servers.

<BR><BR>

A: This can apply to any one or all of the above, but if you're
intentionally or unintentionally with-holding your phone number (CLID -
Caller Line ID), Freeserve will only allow you limited use of their
services. This is an attempt to reduce or prevent any abuse of their
services such as SPAM, etc. You will need to either not use 141 in front
of your phone number or place 1470 in front of it where it could be
affecting you.

</P>

<BR>
<BR>

